Custom Prompt template
   The QuestionAnswerAdvisor uses a default template to augment the user question with the retrieved documents. You can customize this behavior by providing your own PromptTemplate object via the .promptTemplate() builder method. The custom PromptTemplate can use any TemplateRenderer implementation (by default, it uses StPromptTemplate based on the StringTemplate engine).


//custom prompt template
	@GetMapping("/chat1")
	public ResponseEntity<String> chat1(@RequestParam(value = "q", required = true) String query) {
		

		// 1) Build a StTemplateRenderer with custom delimiters and strict validation
		        StTemplateRenderer stRenderer = StTemplateRenderer.builder()
		                .startDelimiterToken('<')            // default is '{'
		                .endDelimiterToken('>')              // default is '}'
		                .validationMode(ValidationMode.THROW) // THROW, WARN, or IGNORE
		                .validateStFunctions()               // allow ST built-ins during validation
		                .build();

		        // 2) Define your template (advisor will inject <context>)
		        String templateText = """
		            You are a helpful assistant. Use ONLY the provided context to answer

		            [INSTRUCTIONS]
		            - If the answer is not found in the context, reply exactly: "No grounded answer available."
		            - Be concise; use bullets when appropriate.
		            - Do not use prior knowledge beyond context.

		            [QUESTION]
		            <query>
		            """;

		        // 3) Create a PromptTemplate that uses StTemplateRenderer
		        PromptTemplate promptTemplate = PromptTemplate.builder()
		                .template(templateText)
		                .renderer(stRenderer)
		                .build();

		        // 4) Build QuestionAnswerAdvisor with search tuning and your template
		        var qaAdvisor = QuestionAnswerAdvisor.builder(vectorStore)
		                .searchRequest(SearchRequest.builder()
		                    .topK(4)
		                    .similarityThreshold(0.60d)
		                    .build())
		                .promptTemplate(promptTemplate)
		          .build(); // advisor will inject <context> from vector search
		   

		
		String str = chatClient.prompt()
				.advisors(qaAdvisor)
				.user(user -> user.text(this.userMessage).param("query", query)).call().content();
		
		return ResponseEntity.ok(str);
	}


