3. Now we create a bean for exposing resources. This bean is going to return a List of SyncMCPResourceSpecification (ie) for every file present in the directory,it will return sync resources specification. And since there can be multiple files in the directory. It has to return a list of sync resource specification.

So in main class


@SpringBootApplication
public class McpServerSseApplication {
	
	@Value("${resource.directory.path}")
    private String directoryPath;

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		SpringApplication.run(McpServerSseApplication.class, args);
	}

	
	@Bean
    public List<McpServerFeatures.SyncResourceSpecification> myResources() {
		//access the path from the application properties
		String path = directoryPath;
		
		//find out all the files which are present in this directory.
		Path folderPath = Paths.get(path);
		
		// Iterate through them and find out the syncResourceSpecification for all of the files. 
		//So I am going to stream on the path and for each path we call a method which give me syncresourcespecification. 
		try(Stream<Path> paths = Files.list(folderPath)) {
            List<McpServerFeatures.SyncResourceSpecification> resources = paths
                    .map(this::getResourceSpecification)
                    .collect(Collectors.toList());

            return resources;
        } catch (IOException e) {
            return Collections.emptyList();
        }
	}
}

- Create getResourceSpecification() which return syncresourcespecification and takes path of the
file as argument. 

private McpServerFeatures.SyncResourceSpecification getResourceSpecification(Path filePath) {
	        String fileName = filePath.getFileName().toString();
	        
	        //generate metadata for this method like file name, absolute path name, file uri and we are going to use when we are creating the document resource
	        Path absolutePath = filePath.toAbsolutePath();
	        String fileUri = "file://" + absolutePath;
	        String mimeType = "text/plain";
	        
	        //Documentresource is a container which holds the metadata for a particular file, created using McpSchema.Resource and we use builder pattern
	        McpSchema.Resource documentResource = McpSchema.Resource.builder()
	                .uri(fileUri)
	                .name(fileName)
	                .description("Document: " + fileName)
	                .mimeType(mimeType).build();
	        
	        //We use SyncResourceSpecification constructor which takes documentresource and BiFunction which takes Exchange, Request and returns ReadResourceResult
	        McpServerFeatures.SyncResourceSpecification spec = new McpServerFeatures.SyncResourceSpecification(documentResource,
	                (exchange, request) -> {
	                    try {
	                    	//read the file
	                        String textContent = Files.readString(absolutePath);
	                        
	                        //generate text resources contents
	                        McpSchema.TextResourceContents textContents = new McpSchema.TextResourceContents(request.uri(), mimeType, textContent);

	                        // return read resource result
	                        return new McpSchema.ReadResourceResult(List.of(textContents));
	                    } catch (IOException e) {
	                        throw new RuntimeException(e);
	                    }
	                });
	        return spec;
	 }

First, we had created a document resource using the metadata of the file like file name, file uri,
mime type, etc. And then we had implemented the bi-function using exchange, request and we returned ReadResourceResult. And finally, we got the sync resource specification that we had to return for that particular file.

